cast.overview: The true story of the inseparable Von Erich brothers, who made history in the intensely competitive world of professional wrestling in the early 1980s. Through tragedy and triumph, under the shadow of their domineering father and coach, the brothers seek larger-than-life immortality on the biggest stage in sports.
cast.title: The Iron Claw

cast.original_title: The Curious Case of Benjamin Button
cast.overview: Born under unusual circumstances, Benjamin Button springs into being as an elderly man in a New Orleans nursing home and ages in reverse. Twelve years after his birth, he meets Daisy, a child who flits in and out of his life as she grows up to be a dancer. Though he has all sorts of unusual adventures over the course of his life, it is his relationship with Daisy, and the hope that they will come together at the right time, that drives Benjamin forward.
cast.title: The Curious Case of Benjamin Button

details.biography: Brett Beoubay is a professionally certified and multi-award-winning safety engineer, responsible for the workplace safety & health of more than 70,000 state government employees. Born and raised in New Orleans, La., he graduated Summa Cum Laude from Jesuit High School, after which he moved to Baton Rouge to attend LSU and receive his Bachelor of Science degree in Occupational Safety and Health. His start in the entertainment industry came at an early age as a children’s clothing model, followed by numerous theater performances. In the past 20 years, this SAG-eligible and Best Supporting Actor nominee has appeared in more than 70 film, TV, stage, web, and commercial productions, including an international spot for NETGEAR that won multiple Golden Addy Awards. His credits also include voice-over projects for radio, animation, and JC Penney as well as appearances in print media and at industrial trade shows.
details.name: Brett Beoubay
